Maldives is at the infant stage of systematically contributing to building resilience to hazards due to various factors and one being Disaster Management was not a top priority until the lessons learnt from the Tsunami in the region. Other challenges include:
?	No clear mandates for coordination, monitoring and reporting;
?	Inadequate funding and at times financial restrictions and shortfalls;
?	Inadequate human capacity in terms of new and emerging disaster preparedness, prevention and response under DRR strategies as well as limited technical expertise available in country; 
?	No legal framework on DRR is a major setback in a lot of the national initiatives on DRR; and
?	Political instability due to the transition phase of Maldives towards a democratic and decentralized government system with the enabling policy and legislative frameworks.

